Chrysler Corp. of the United States and Japan's  Isuzu Motors Ltd. told the transport ministry Thursday they would recall some  5,200 defective vehicles, officials said.
Chrysler is to recall 3,410 of its Jeep Cherokee and 655 of Jeep Grand  Cherokee imported between September 1992 and August last year, while Isuzu is  recalling 1,139 of its U-CXG 23 series.
They said Chrysler would fix radiator hoses in the Cherokee, which could  contact with fan belt and break it, and steering and ignition systems in the  Grand Cherokee, while Isuzu would correct battery wiring.
